description.narrative: Government welfare institutions and CSOs have the capacity to deliver protection services to children (boys and girls), including during humanitarian situations., which contributes to Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, increased numbers of children in Somalia are protected from all forms of abuse, neglect and exploitation

description.narrative: UNICEF reached a total of 236,772 people in IDP and host communities with emergency child protection services delivering mental health and psychosocial services, community reintegration, family tracing, and gender-based violence. UNICEF contributed to continuity of service provision during COVID 19 and adjusted service delivery modalities to met the challenging environment. | Status:Met | As-of Date:09/01/2021
